README - Portable Markdown to HTML Note Builder
===============================================

This is a simple, portable template for writing notes in Markdown (.md)
and converting them to clean HTML with custom CSS and LaTeX math support
(using MathJax).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIREMENTS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Python 3 must be installed.
   - Test by running: python3 --version

2. The 'markdown' Python package must be installed.
   - Install via pip:
     pip install markdown

No other dependencies are required.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
FILES INCLUDED
----------------------------------------------------------------------

- notes.md         → Your main Markdown note file
- template.html    → HTML template with placeholders for title and content
- style.css        → Your custom styling for the output
- build.py         → Python script that converts .md to .html
- MyMarkdown.sublime-build → Build system for Sublime Text (optional)

Output:
- output.html      → The generated HTML file

----------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

### OPTION A: Use Sublime Text (recommended)

1. Open the folder in Sublime.
2. Open notes.md.
3. Go to: Tools → Build System → MyMarkdown.
4. Press Ctrl+B (or Cmd+B on Mac).
5. Your notes will be built to 'output.html' and optionally opened in your browser.

### OPTION B: Use terminal (manual)

1. Navigate to the folder.
2. Run:
   python3 build.py

This will generate output.html in the same folder.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTES ON MARKDOWN FEATURES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

- Regular Markdown formatting works: # Headings, lists, links, etc.
- MathJax support is enabled:
  Use \\( inline math \\) and \\[ display math \\]

- YouTube videos can be embedded using iframe:
  Example:

  <iframe width="560" height="315"
    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
    frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

----------------------------------------------------------------------
TROUBLESHOOTING
----------------------------------------------------------------------

• If the build system fails with "python: command not found":
  → Try changing the Sublime build file to use "python3" instead.

• If Math doesn't render:
  → Make sure to use \\( ... \\) or \\[ ... \\] (double backslashes).

• If the iframe video doesn't show:
  → Ensure you're using the embed URL format:
     https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID                                                                                                     

----------------------------------------------------------------------
CONTACT / ATTRIBUTION
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Template designed for portability and simplicity.
Feel free to customize or expand it.

